questions.explanation:
In the **Object Adapter** pattern, the Adapter maintains compatibility with the client by implementing the **Target** interface (or subclassing the Target class). Unlike the Class Adapter which uses inheritance, the Object Adapter uses **composition**, meaning it holds an instance of the **Adaptee** to delegate requests to it. Thus, statements A and C are correct.

```mermaid
classDiagram
    class Target {
        <<interface>>
        +request()
    }
    class Adapter {
        -adaptee: Adaptee
        +request()
    }
    class Adaptee {
        +specificRequest()
    }
    Target <|.. Adapter
    Adapter --> Adaptee
```

