questions.explanation:
The Composite design pattern is designed to represent part-whole hierarchies so that clients can treat individual objects and compositions of objects uniformly.

- **Component (`FileSystemItem`)**: An abstract class or interface that declares the interface for objects in the composition (e.g., `getSize()`).
- **Leaf (`TextFile`, `BinaryFile`, `Shortcut`)**: Represents individual objects in the composition that have no children.
- **Composite (`Folder`)**: Represents a container that can store both Leaves and other Composites. It implements the child-related operations (`add`, `remove`) and the component interface by delegating tasks to its children.

```mermaid
classDiagram
    class FileSystemItem {
        <<abstract>>
        +getSize() int
    }
    class TextFile {
        +getSize() int
    }
    class BinaryFile {
        +getSize() int
    }
    class Shortcut {
        +getSize() int
    }
    class Folder {
        -items: List<FileSystemItem>
        +getSize() int
        +addItem(item: FileSystemItem)
        +removeItem(item: FileSystemItem)
    }
    FileSystemItem <|-- TextFile
    FileSystemItem <|-- BinaryFile
    FileSystemItem <|-- Shortcut
    FileSystemItem <|-- Folder
    Folder o-- FileSystemItem : children
```

